th sides are unwelcome or were in polite discussion, what filled the void? Well, someone like a Nick Fuentes who says, well, Jews are in these positions because they're fucking evil right because they're just evil sons of bitches who like know how to take advantage of gentiles and there's really no other explanation for this and because he's saying these edgy things and he's noticing patterns not just that pattern but many other patterns suddenly he has way more credibility than he would have had in a world in which people are allowed to to talk about these things openly. And I'll just add one other thing to allow people to speak openly about things whether it's in academia on social media etc is not to say that A, you approve of all of those standpoints. Of course, that's so ridiculous that anyone would think that that means you give it a stamp of approval. And B, the idea that in some sense you're doing this or you talk about a thing because you're motivated by hatred of a different group or hatred of the opposite idea. It might be true in some cases, right? Actually, it probably is true for some people. But that's not a reason then to taboo it it's actually a reason to do the reverse so that in the end we can come to a consensus hopefully that tends to be closer to the truth rather than further away from it.

